# C Data Types 
**Overview**
- C data types are defined as the data storage format that a variable can store a data to perform a specific operation.
- Data types are used to define a variable before to use in a program.
- Size of a variable, constant and array are determined by data types.

Four Data Types in C Language:
	<pre><table>
		<tr><th>Type</th><th>Data Types</th></tr>
		<tr><td>Basic data types</td><td>int, char, float, double</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Derived data type</td><td>pointer, array, structure, union</td> 
		</tr> 
	</table></pre>

